# biom3sync excludes — patterns relative to the data/ root.
#
# Copy this file to config/excludes (which is gitignored) and edit it to
# exclude paths from push, pull, and diff:
#
#     cp config/excludes.example config/excludes
#
# Customizations to config/excludes survive `git pull` because the live
# file is not tracked. To pick up new recommended patterns from upstream,
# diff this .example file against your local copy and merge by hand.
#
# Syntax follows rsync filter rules. One pattern per line. Lines beginning
# with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Examples:
#   nm-team-data/          # skip an entire subdirectory
#   *.tmp.npy              # skip a file glob anywhere under data/
#   /scratch/              # anchor to data/ root (leading slash)

